<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41037d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41037d">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41037d"> 37(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> estate by the / curtesy</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">If, however, the husband had issue by the wife who could inherit the property as her heir, on the death of the wife, the husband became entitled to her property for the rest of his life, in priority to the wife&apos;s heir or other person entitled; such estate was known as an <mark>estate &ldquo;by the curtesy.&rdquo;</mark> <small> Maud I. Crofts, <a name="MICW" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MICW"><cite title="source">Women under English Law</cite></a>, 1st ed. (1925) 34</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
